            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ [ ¶ The other day, a few minutes after I had shot a brush turkey, in the dense brush of the Upper Orara River, ¶ NSW, near Grafton. ¶  I came upon a beautiful flowering tree which, with a large exp...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">84.04.00</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From [Edith Thornton]</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found. The text given here is from a letter 'from a correspondent' to the <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Daily telegraph</seg> (Sydney), 19 April 1884, p. 9.</p>
               </note>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[<seg style="">The other day, a few minutes after I had shot a brush turkey, in the dense brush of the Upper Orara River,</seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                     <p rend="Footnote"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>NSW, near Grafton.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> I came upon a beautiful flowering tree which, with a large experience among the brushes of the colony, I had never seen before. <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>…</seg>
               <note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The omitted text is a description of a tree with large scarlet flowers, almost certainly <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Stenocarpus sinuatus</seg>, a specimen of which, recorded as collected by Miss E. Thornton at the Orara River in 1884, is now in the National Herbarium of Victoria (MEL 676462).</p>
               </note>
               <seg style=""> I have sent specimens to Mr. Moore of the Botanical Gardens, Sydney, and to Baron von Mueller, of Melbourne.]</seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
      </body>
